# Presence users and locations

Home-automation **presence** (My Tracks / OwnTracks people on the map) is modeled as **users** with **locations**, not participants with fixes.

## Use

| Concept | Name | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Stable id from My Tracks | `user_id` | `henrique`, `kristen` |
| Roster row | `User` / `UserRecord` / `UserOut` | SQLite `rule_users` |
| Name fields | `first_name`, `last_name`, `display_name` | `display_name` defaults to `first_name` on sync |
| Latest GPS reading | `location` / `UserLocation` | SQLite `rule_user_last_location` |
| Location history | `UserLocationHistory` | SQLite `rule_user_location_history` |
| Rule conditions | `users_inside_geofence`, `users_outside_geofence` | `user_ids: string[]` |
| HTTP routes | `/v1/rules/users`, `/v1/rules/users/status` | |
| Webhook body field | `user_id` | |

## Do not use (presence domain)

- `participant`, `participant_id`, `participant_ids`
- `fix`, `last_fix`, `upsert_*_fix`, `*_fixes`
- `participants_inside_geofence`, `participants_outside_geofence`
- `min_fix_accuracy_m` → use `min_location_accuracy_m`

## UI display

- Rules and APIs store **`user_id`** only.
- UI labels use **`display_name`** from the user roster (synced from My Tracks; defaults to `first_name`).
- Do not show raw `user_id` when a roster row exists.

## Exceptions

- **Third-party wire formats** (my-tracks admin API JSON keys, MQTT topic segments) may still say `participant` until upstream renames — map at the integration boundary only; domesti-bot schemas, stores, and UI use `user` / `location`.
- **Device discovery** (`device_state_watcher`, Kasa, etc.) is unrelated — do not rename device polling to “location”.

## Sync semantics

My Tracks sync **replaces** the full user roster each run (`replace_users`), preserving `user_id` from My Tracks `username`. Parse `first_name` / `last_name` from the export `display_name`; set `display_name = first_name` unless a future UI overrides it.
